tasks.description:
Update `apps/web/src/app/robots.ts` to add AI crawler-specific rules. Block aggressive scrapers (CCBot, Bytespider) while explicitly allowing beneficial ones (GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot). Also disallow `/test/` routes.

## Complete File Content

Replace the entire file with:

```typescript
import type { MetadataRoute } from 'next'
import { siteConfig } from '@/config/site'

export default function robots(): MetadataRoute.Robots {
  return {
    rules: [
      // Default: allow all crawlers
      {
        userAgent: '*',
        allow: '/',
        disallow: ['/api/', '/_next/', '/test/'],
      },
      // Allow beneficial AI crawlers explicitly
      {
        userAgent: 'GPTBot',
        allow: '/',
        disallow: ['/api/', '/_next/', '/test/'],
      },
      {
        userAgent: 'ClaudeBot',
        allow: '/',
        disallow: ['/api/', '/_next/', '/test/'],
      },
      {
        userAgent: 'PerplexityBot',
        allow: '/',
        disallow: ['/api/', '/_next/', '/test/'],
      },
      // Block aggressive scrapers
      {
        userAgent: 'CCBot',
        disallow: '/',
      },
      {
        userAgent: 'Bytespider',
        disallow: '/',
      },
    ],
    sitemap: `${siteConfig.url}/sitemap.xml`,
  }
}
```

## Changes from Current File

1. The default `*` user agent now disallows `/test/` in addition to `/api/` and `/_next/`
2. Three new beneficial AI crawler rules are added (GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot) with explicit allow
3. Two aggressive scraper rules are added (CCBot, Bytespider) with full disallow
4. The `sitemap` field references `siteConfig.url` for the sitemap URL

## Acceptance Criteria

1. Visiting `/robots.txt` shows the updated rules
2. CCBot and Bytespider are fully disallowed (`Disallow: /`)
3. GPTBot, ClaudeBot, and PerplexityBot are explicitly allowed with the same disallow list as the default agent
4. `/test/` is disallowed for all user agents
5. The sitemap URL points to `https://dorkos.ai/sitemap.xml`
